title: For Sale:  SIG 522
postcontent:
SIG 522 Heavy Barrel model.
five Black Dog metal feed lip 25 round mags.
One SIG factory 10 round mag.
One custom barrel nut for installing an AR style floating hand guard - not pictured.
One set of scope rings - not pictured.
One plastic gun case.

I bought this SIG 522 Heavy Barrel model a few yrs ago thinking it would be good to have two .22 rifles so family could go with me to the range. Reality: that is not working out, I still always go by myself and I have a custom ruger 10/22 I always take so this gun has been to the range once, had 150 rounds fired, then cleaned and sat in the case ever since.

It is a Heavy barrel SIG 522 model so it is more accurate then the regular SIG 522 models. One great thing about these Sig 522 guns, they eat any ammo without constantly jamming. You can research this with a google search [sig 522 reliability] - these SIG 522 guns really run trouble free with every type of ammo out there.

When I shot this gun at the range it ran perfect, no jams with cheap Remington golden bullet ammo. I ordered five black dog 25 round mags with the metal feed lips for it and these are included in the sale along with the factory 10 round mag.

You can load all these mags up and power through 125 rounds in under 60 seconds if you want to show off or take your time and drive tacks with this baby. No way you can shoot that fast with a finicky Ruger 10/22. If I did not already have so much invested in my custom Ruger 10/22 I would never sell this SIG 522, I love how it shoots so reliably and accurate.

I also have a custom barrel nut [not pictured] that allows a AR style floating hand guard to be installed, this barrel nut was never installed but is included in the sale. 

I have 1 set of medium height 30mm scope rings that will be included with this sale. If you want to use a 1" scope you can get inserts to reduce the 30mm down to 1". No pictures of the rings as this web site restricts you to only 3 photos if you are not a dealer. 

I have about 675.00 into it and it is almost brand new. I am selling to fund the purchase of a SA 1911 pistol.

No shipping, local sale only in wa state. Trades possibly accepted, Hit me up with what you got, looking for SA 1911 .45 pistol. I am firm on the price due to the gun being almost new along with the included accessories. Terms of deal include complying with Initiative 594. postcontent:
Walther CCP w/Stainless Slide - hard to find carry sized 9mm w/new "Softcoil" system - $420 (MSRP $489)
 
Fenton, MO - pickup w/background check or transfer only
 
The all new CCP (Concealed Carry Pistol) in 9mm Luger has an ideal combination of style, ergonomics, size, shape, accuracy, and ability to conceal comfortably.  The new Walther SOFTCOIL ™ gas-delayed blowback technology works to make the CCP an excellent concealed carry firearm.
 
The CCP’s SOFTCOIL™ gas-delayed blowback system uses gas pressure from the ignited cartridge by directing it through a small port in the barrel in front of the chamber to slow down and delay the rearward motion of the slide. This is accomplished by means of a piston contained inside of a cylinder located under the barrel that opposes the rearward motion of the slide until the gas pressure has declined after the bullet has left the barrel.  This allows the slide to end its rearward motion, opening the breech, and ejecting the empty cartridge case.
 
Benefits of Walther SOFTCOIL ™ Technology
 
It allows the slide to be easily manipulated to chamber a round.
Barrel rise is reduced up to one third less than similar pistols.
Decrease barrel rise helps you remain focused to accurately hit your target shot after shot.

title: For Sale:  Remington 870 Express Deer Slayer
postcontent:
This Remington 870 Express Deer Slayer has two barrels:  It has a 25in smoothbore, vented ribbed for the birds and buckshot.  And, instead of the traditional slug barrel that comes with a 24in Mossberg Rifled Slug barrel that has a scope mount, is ported for recoil reduction and quicker sight alignment after a shot, with a 1-in-36in twist on the rifling.
No scope mount is more accurate for a shotgun than one integrated with the barrel!
This has been my hunting shotgun for several years, but only used for deer hunting.  It does show some wear and tear.  A few scratches on the stock and there was some rust on the vented barrel that has been removed.  This is why there is a reduced price.
I've looked on Guns America and Gunbroker and set a price lower than any I could find on those websites or Armslist because of the wear and tear.
I've taken several bucks with heartshots using that rifled barrel and have yet to miss a shot taken in the field.

title: For Sale:  9mm Sig-Sauer P239 DA/SA, comes with five mags
postcontent:
I've got a 9mm DA/SA Sig-Sauer P239 for sale. According to the serial number guide I found this is a mid-90s pistol (SN# SA23xxx) meaning it predates the decline in QC that the Sig product line saw in the 2000s. Pistol is in good shape overall and shoots great but has some finish wear on the barrel and sharp edges of the slide. Comes with five genuine Sig OEM magazines, blue SigArms plastic case, and a universal P-series manual.

This is a fantastic pistol for women or anyone else that has trouble properly gripping a fullsize double-stack. Don't get me wrong because I don't mean that in some dumb "durr hurr wimmin cain't handle no real gun" sort of way but rather that the frame size, slim grip, and control ergonomics are great for people with smaller hands. On top of that the all-metal construction gives it added heft and thus controllability when compared to similarly sized polymer-framed pistols, with the extra mass helping to soak up recoil. This was my wife's favorite pistol when she started shooting, and later on it was always the first centerfire pistol she handed to her friends when she brought them to their first range experience. 

At the same time since it's slightly larger than what's considered a compact frame by modern standard, it's also not too small for those with larger hands who'd prefer a slim and all-metal EDC.

Devastating, authoritative knockdown power! The Sumatra 2500 is an easy-to-cock, lever-action repeater. This precharged pneumatic (PCP) has two built-in chambers (290cc total) that hold high-pressure air (3,000 psi) from a scuba tank (Included), hand pump or compressor.

It has a two-stage adjustable trigger. The sights are pretty unique, in that both the front and rear are adjustable. The front post can be adjusted for elevation by turning a small wheel under the post. The rear is a two-hole aperture that flips from a small to large hole and is adjustable for windage.

Accuracy is the name of the game when it comes to shooting, and the Sumatra 2500 excels in that area: 3/8" ctc at 30 yds. with Eun Jin pellets. To get the most from this airgun, you'll want to mount a scope on the 11mm dovetails. The finely rifled (and 10x1mm threaded) steel barrel (1:18 RH twist) is fed by a 6-shot cylinder that makes for quick follow-up shots. The cylinder makes it easy to use longer pellets and even mix-and-match different pellet lengths and types.

The adjustable power wheel has 13 settings, making this one of the most versatile powerhouses on the market! You'll get about 11 shots on high power and 18 on medium.

Includes probe with 1/8" BSPP male threads and 2 rotary clips. The high pressure connector and gauge is included to connect the gun to the scuba tank. A hard Plano rifle case (PL1502-01) is strongly suggested!

title: For Sale:  CZ52 7.62x25. Exc. shape and shooter. All #'s match.
postcontent:
Very nice CZ52. Two mags and the cleaning rod included. Has original phosphate finish showing some handling marks, but still looks great. Internals in excellent condition. All the numbers match. Has original plastic grips in very good condition with no cracks. Gun has a decocker. This thing sounds like a 357 when you fire it. The rounds are going around 1600 fps muzzle velocity. It makes a great fireball too.  They bearing setup and balance of the gun make it have minimal recoil.  You can unload it as fast as you can pull the trigger, and never worry about a misfire or jam. Ammo is really cheap too.  Loud, incredibly powerful, reliable, breaks down in seconds, and cheap to shoot--its like a handheld AK.

I researched all the markings and came up with the following: the phosphate instead of blued finish indicates it wasn't a refurbished pistol. The crossed swords and number 53 indicate it is Czech Army and made in 53, the "rid" also incidates it was army production, not civilian. The circled T on the barrel inside the chamber indicates it passed military inspection for safety and the de-cocker passed. The various other marks are for the workers who might have assembled it and the circled vot or vor is probably the plant that did any refinishing or work on it before it was sent back out into the world.

There are no import marks that I can find. They should be on the bottom of the frame between the trigger guard and the end of the barrel. Oh well, it is simply a very nice looking and shooting pistol. Kinda looks like what the desert eagle might have been imagined to look like in the 50's for some sci-fi movie.

$275 and I'll throw in 100 rounds of ammo.

515 6six4 5978
